<h1>@HI{{yasui}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @Vmasustem{{}} <strong>@HI{{yasui}}</strong>
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{yasui}}</strong> is an auxiliary that adds a nuance of "easy to do".
</p>

<p>
The combined form functions as an @HI{{i}}-adjective and inflects in the same way.
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kono @KJ{{sino-^character}}ha @KJ{{memorize}}e<strong>yasui</strong>desu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      This kanji is easy to remember.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kono @KT{{pen}}ha kaki<strong>yasui</strong>desu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      This pen is easy to write with.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

